data.description: Great opportunity to own property with no zoning, no covenants, no HOA, and you could have a business (buyer to verify).  Has a huge insulated and concrete floor SHOP, allows horses and it is near the famous Gallatin River and much closer to Belgrade than Manhattan. This well kept property boasts a 30'x56' shop with 3 stalls that include 2 tall doors to store your RV or camper, an 8x12 horse loafing shed, and 1.91 acres which borders state land on the back east side.  There is 220 power for RV parking. The large back yard and pasture gives a restful oasis to relax and enjoy. The original home was built in 1959 and the new addition was added in 1998 to give it about 3076 sq.ft. (buyer to verify) on the main level with a few stairs plus an attached garage. The living room has a wood stove that can easily be converted to a gas stove. The kitchen includes custom made cabinets, an eating area, and a nice picture window. There are 2 bedrooms and a full bath down the hallway. Laundry is on the main level too.  The master bedroom is separate from the main living area and includes a bathroom and walk in closet. In the back of the home is a family room with access to the patio, plus another room that could be used as an office or flex room.  The basement has one bedroom or flex room, utility room, and storage room.  Carpets have just been shampooed. Sit on the front porch and take in the mountain view plus the beauty of the landscaped front yard with colorful flowers. This property is in the Manhattan/Amsterdam school district, buyer to verify. There are numerous possibilities for this property!
